1.title: Joe and Gia
1.plot: When it comes to buying hunting and fishing property in our nation's heartland, nothing beats a real estate company made up of hunters and fisherman. The guys at Whitetail Properties have the leading edge on where to buy the perfect piece of land, a gem of a country home or even an entire hunting lodge. They don't just take their buyers on a house tour; they go an extreme adventure to give them a hands-on instruction guide to Living Country.

2.title: Nick and Alisha, Baby on the Way
2.plot: With a baby on the way, Nick and Alisha need to find their dream home, fast! These lifelong hunters want a modern house and a fishing pond on a 100-acre hunting property that's private, but not too remote. Are they asking too much? Pete and Dan compete to sell them the perfect property, but Nick & Alisha's decision surprises everyone!

3.title: Jodi and Paige Outdoors in Illinois
3.plot: Jodi and Paige know exactly what they want, a secluded 100-acre plot with a pond and good hunting? and a turnkey house with a deck? and a wood burning stove. Are they asking too much? Pete and Dan show off their outdoor skills in a quest to convince these selective buyers to purchase the right property.

4.title: Darrell and Debbie's New Kentucky Home
4.plot: It's a family affair when Kentuckians Darrell and Debbie decide to buy recreational land they can pass down to future generations. Will it have electricity or plumbing , or will it be as rustic as it gets? Their son Justin acts as their agent and struggles to make their dreams come true ? with a little help from Whitetail Properties' very own Pete and Dan.
